{
  "info": {
    "name": "TaskTracker - Iteration 1",
    "description": "Docker + PostgreSQL + Domain + Health-check validation tests for TaskTracker Iteration 1\n\nIteráció 1 tesztek:\n- Health-check endpoint tesztelése adatbázis csatlakozással\n- API response shape validálása (success + data)\n- HTTP status kódok ellenőrzése\n- Response headers validálása\n- Adatbázis csatlakozási érvényesítés\n- Response time teljesítmény validálása\n- EF Core DbContext működési ellenőrzése",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "version": "1.0.0"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health Check",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "// Status code validation",
              "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
              "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Response time validation",
              "pm.test('Response time is less than 2000ms (first request can be slower due to EF Core)', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(2000);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Parse response body",
              "const responseJson = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "// Validate response structure has 'success' property",
              "pm.test('Response has success property', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(responseJson).to.have.property('success');",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Validate success property is boolean",
              "pm.test('Success property is a boolean', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(responseJson.success).to.be.a('boolean');",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Validate response has 'data' property",
              "pm.test('Response has data property', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(responseJson).to.have.property('data');",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Validate data is an object",
              "pm.test('Data property is an object', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(responseJson.data).to.be.an('object');",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Validate the success value is true",
              "pm.test('Health-check returns success: true', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(responseJson.success).to.equal(true);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Validate response headers",
              "pm.test('Content-Type is application/json', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('application/json');",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Validate response structure is valid JSON",
              "pm.test('Response is valid JSON', function () {",
              "  pm.response.to.be.json;",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Validate response body length",
              "pm.test('Response size is less than 5KB', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(pm.response.text().length).to.be.below(5120);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Database connectivity indication",
              "pm.test('Response indicates successful API initialization with EF Core', function () {",
              "  pm.expect(responseJson.success).to.be.true;",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Accept",
            "value": "application/json",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
          "host": [
            "{{baseUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            ""
          ]
        },
        "description": "Health-check endpoint with PostgreSQL + EF Core integration.\n\nIteráció 1 követelmények:\n- Docker Compose PostgreSQL konténer fut\n- EF Core DbContext konfigurálva van\n- Initial migration lefutott\n- User entitás kialakult\n\nExpected response format:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {}\n}\n```\n\nEz a végpont igazolja, hogy az alkalmazás elérhető, az adatbázis csatlakozásként működik, és az API response shape helyesen van konfigurálva."
      },
      "response": [
        {
          "name": "Success - Health Check with Database",
          "originalRequest": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
